GlassFish - JDBC Resources

- Create/configure JDBC Connection Pool by going to Resources > JDBC > JDBC Resources

(i) Create jdbc/admin JDBC Resource

Click the New button > New JDBC Resource

- JNDI Name: jdbc/admin
- Pool Name: adminPool

Click OK

(ii) jdbc/cs JDBC Resource

Click the New button > New JDBC Resource

- JNDI Name: jdbc/cs
- Pool Name: adminPool

Click OK

(iii) jdbc/merchant JDBC Resource

Click the New button > New JDBC Resource

- JNDI Name: jdbc/merchant
- Pool Name: merchantPool

Click OK

(iv) Create jbdc/paygate

Click the New button > New JDBC Resource

- JNDI Name: jdbc/paygate
- Pool Name: post-gre-sql_paygate_payuserPool

Click OK

(v) Create jbdc/dc JDBC Resource

Click the New button > New JDBC Resource

- JNDI Name: jdbc/dc
- Pool Name: paypool

Click OK

